---
description: Performance and data-loading conventions for Scriptony (timeline, lists, new features)
---

# Scriptony performance (SPA)

- **One batch per domain**: Prefer `ultraBatchLoadProject` / shared helpers in `src/lib/timeline-map.ts` instead of chained `getActs` → `getAllSequences` → … calls. New timeline-related features should use `useProjectTimeline` + `queryKeys.timeline.byProject` so React Query owns cache and prefetch.

- **No full-panel blocking loaders**: Large sections (e.g. Structure & Beats) should use skeletons, stale-while-revalidate, or a slim banner — not a single empty state that hides the whole tree while data loads.

- **Prefetch**: Project list / cards may prefetch on hover (see `prefetchProjectTimeline`, `ProjectCardWithPrefetch`, Projects list `Card`).

- **Payload size**: When the API supports it, use structure-only loads (`excludeContent` / `loadTimelineStructure`) for huge book payloads before pulling full scene content.
